network_overview: The capture contains only two short IMS registration attempts over the Gm interface (SIP/SCTP). Both transactions complete with 200 OK, yet the analytics engine flags them as “FAILED – SETUP_TIMEOUT”, indicating a false-positive classification rather than a real network fault.

observations.finding: Two independent SIP REGISTER dialogs (call-id asbc47zRmWaCXwykhNhFzykadYy4 & asbcqzdo4HG9RSkfPCNfIvTgvw9H) complete in <130 ms each, well within IMS specs.
No INVITE/BYE seen; therefore no bearer (QCI=1) or RTP was established. No media-plane issues can exist.
Tool incorrectly marks successful 200 OK as FAILED/SETUP_TIMEOUT; this is an instrumentation defect, not a call drop.

root_causes.issue: False-positive SETUP_TIMEOUT alarms on successful REGISTER
root_causes.description: The KPI engine treats any dialog without a subsequent INVITE within a hard-coded window as a failed call, even though the REGISTER succeeded.
root_causes.impact: Inflates drop counters, triggers unnecessary tickets, and masks real failures.

recommendations.action: Fix analytics rule-set: separate REGISTRATION success from CALL_SETUP success; use INVITE/BYE presence to classify calls.
recommendations.rationale: Removes noise, improves MTTR for genuine voice failures.

recommendations.action: Enable SIP call-id correlation across P-CSCF logs to confirm no INVITE followed.
recommendations.rationale: Validates the capture conclusion and fine-tunes heuristics.

session_analysis.signaling_health: SIP/SCTP transport healthy (no retransmissions, 200 OK returned).
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No user-plane traffic observed (no GTP-U, no RTP).
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Only control-plane registration occurred; bearer setup would start after subsequent INVITE.
